OL,3,CDetectorists unearth up to 15,000
OL,4,CRoman coins in North Wales
OL,6,FSix weeks ago, whilst detecting with
OL,7,Fhis friend Ian Nicholson, Mr Moss
OL,8,Freceived a faint but steady signal
OL,9,Ffrom his new detector, originating
OL,10,Ffrom a depth of over half a metre.
OL,12,FHe said: "At that depth, I expected it
OL,13,Fto be iron, but I dug down and saw the
OL,14,Fedge of a clay pot filled with coins.
OL,15,FMy heart stopped...I sat there in
OL,16,Fshock and started shouting over to
OL,17,FIan."
