OL,3,CDetectorists unearth up to 15,000
OL,4,CRoman coins in North Wales
OL,6,FThe pair called the Finds Liaison
OL,7,FOfficer for Wrexham to declare the
OL,8,Fdiscovery, who advised that because
OL,9,Fthe coins were in a vulnerable area,
OL,10,Fclose to public footpaths, they would
OL,11,Fneed to conduct the excavation
OL,12,Fthemselves.
OL,14,FAfter six hours of digging and
OL,15,Fcarefully removing the coins from the
OL,16,Farea, all whilst recording each
OL,17,Fdiscovery in a note pad and with video
OL,18,Ffootage, Mr Moss took the coins home
OL,19,Fto address, before driving them down
OL,20,Fto the museum.
